---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you do plumbing for new builds in Officer?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes &mdash; Officer's Arena and Timbertop estates are a constant stream of new homes, and we handle new-build fit-off, hot water connection, gas connection and the warranty plumbing that follows hand-over. We meet South East Water connection and backflow requirements and issue a Certificate of Compliance on the prescribed work." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you offer emergency plumbing in Officer?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes &mdash; 24/7 emergency plumbing across Officer 3809 for burst pipes, no hot water, gas leaks and flooding. New builds are not immune: failed builder-grade flexi-hoses and tap connections are a common early cause of flooding in brand-new estate homes. Call (03) 9003 0108 any time." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you connect a new hot water system and gas in an Officer new build?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes &mdash; we install and connect gas, electric, heat-pump and solar hot water and connect gas cooktops, heaters and BBQ points in Officer new builds, all to AS/NZS 3500 and AS/NZS 5601 with a Certificate of Compliance. Many Officer roofs are solar-ready, so a heat-pump hot water unit paired with daytime solar is a popular, cheap-to-run choice." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does a plumber cost in Officer?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Standard call-out and first hour is $130-$220 ($180-$330 after hours), a new hot water connection $1,400-$3,200 fitted, and a gas point or appliance connection $250-$650 plus the appliance. Worked example: an Officer new-build owner adding an outdoor gas BBQ bayonet and a garden tap usually pays around $450-$700 including the runs, connections, a gas leak test and a Certificate of Compliance." }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="Plumber Officer | New Builds, Emergency, Hot Water, Gas | (03) 9003 0108"
  canonical="https://pakenhamplumbers.com.au/officer/"
  description="Local plumber for Officer 3809 &mdash; new-build fit-off &amp; warranty plumbing, 24/7 emergency, hot water &amp; gas connection. Arena &amp; Timbertop growth-corridor estates. VBA-licensed, South East Water compliant, CoC on every job.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Officer &middot; Arena &middot; Timbertop &middot; 3809</span>
      <h1>Plumber in <span class="accent">Officer</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Officer is new-build country &mdash; the Arena and Timbertop estates are adding
        homes constantly as part of the Cardinia growth corridor. That means new fit-off,
        new hot water and gas connections, builder-warranty plumbing, and the early
        failures (flexi-hoses, tap connections) that even brand-new homes can throw up.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Officer</span>
      <h2>The Officer plumbing story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>A new-build engine room.</h3>
        <p>
          The Cardinia corridor adds roughly 255 new dwellings a year, and a big share of
          that is Officer&rsquo;s Arena and Timbertop estates. Every new house needs
          fit-off, a hot water unit, gas connection and the South East Water connection and
          backflow-prevention sign-off &mdash; with a Certificate of Compliance on the
          prescribed work. We do this work daily.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">New hot water &amp; gas connections.</h3>
        <p>
          New Officer homes get a fresh <a href="/services/hot-water-systems/">hot water
          system</a> and gas connection. Many roofs are solar-ready, so a rebate-eligible
          heat-pump unit paired with daytime solar is a popular, cheap-to-run choice. We
          also connect gas cooktops, heaters and outdoor BBQ points &mdash; licensed
          <a href="/services/gas-fitting/">gas fitting</a> to AS/NZS 5601 with a CoC.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">New builds still have emergencies.</h3>
        <p>
          A brand-new estate home is not immune to a 2am flood. Failed builder-grade
          braided flexi-hoses and loose tap connections are a common early cause of
          flooding in new Officer homes. We attend
          <a href="/services/emergency-plumber/">24/7</a>, isolate fast and replace the
          failed part with a quality unit &mdash; and we recommend checking flexi-hoses
          within the first couple of years.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Warranty &amp; first-fixes.</h3>
        <p>
          In the first years after hand-over, small things surface &mdash; a weeping
          connection, a slow-draining waste, a dripping mixer. We sort these out cleanly
          and can advise whether something falls under your builder&rsquo;s warranty before
          you pay for it.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Officer jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>New-build hot water + gas connection with CoC</li>
          <li>Heat-pump hot water paired with solar &mdash; ~$2,800&ndash;$4,500 before rebates</li>
          <li>Outdoor gas BBQ bayonet + garden tap &mdash; ~$450&ndash;$700</li>
          <li>Failed builder-grade flexi-hose flooding &mdash; 24/7 emergency</li>
          <li>Early-life <a href="/services/burst-leaking-pipes/">leak</a> and fixture fixes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-lakes/">Cardinia Lakes</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/lakeside/">Lakeside</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/heritage-springs/">Heritage Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-shire/">All Cardinia Shire</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Need a plumber in Officer?</h2>
        <p>New builds, emergencies, hot water and gas &mdash; licensed, compliant, CoC on every job.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
